golden-yellow rind, 6 lb, 6\" diameter", "flesh_fruit": "White, sweet, spicy, fragrant", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "Thrives in hot, dry climates. Long storage life. Suitable for Brisbane if given warmest location.", "availability": "Heirloom seed companies", "sort_order": 9}, {"name": "Piel de Sapo (Santa Claus/Christmas Melon)", "slug": "piel-de-sapo-santa-claus-christmas-melon", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Spain (Protected Geographical Indication)", "traits": "Oblong, green-striped mottled rind (''toad skin''), 7-9 lb, 11\" × 7\", thick rind", "flesh_fruit": "Pale green to white, mild sweet honeydew flavor, succulent", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 10}, {"name": "Crenshaw (Cranshaw)", "slug": "crenshaw-cranshaw", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "USA (Casaba × Persian melon hybrid)", "traits": "Large oblong, pointed stem end, smooth golden-yellow green skin, 6-10 lb", "flesh_fruit": "Pale orange to salmon-pink, very sweet with spicy undertones, creamy", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "Known as ''Cadillac of Melons''. Rich aromatic flavor. Requires warm conditions. Can be grown in Brisbane with adequate heat. Must be cut from vine (does not slip).", "availability": "Seed suppliers", "sort_order": 11}, {"name": "Galia (Tropical Melon)", "slug": "galia-tropical-melon", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Israel, 1970s (Honeydew × Cantaloupe cross)", "traits": "Round, netted golden-tan rind like cantaloupe, 3-5 lb", "flesh_fruit": "Thick lime-green, smooth, tropical fruit flavor with banana-like aroma, spicy-sweet", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "Excellent powdery mildew resistance. Well-adapted to subtropical conditions. Popular in markets. Combines best of honeydew and cantaloupe traits.", "availability": "Widely available, Australian nurseries", "sort_order": 12}, {"name": "M