an tropical conditions. Dense netting protects fruit in monsoon.", "availability": "Konico Seeds dealers, Farmers Stop, Kerala agricultural suppliers", "sort_order": 3}, {"name": "Crispy (Hybrid F1) 🧬", "slug": "crispy-hybrid-f1", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "India (Konico Seeds)", "traits": "Round, cream-white skin with dense netting, 1-1.5 kg", "flesh_fruit": "Orange, sweet taste, firm texture", "yield_notes": "High productivity", "growing_notes": "Hard rind with good keeping quality. Tolerant to melon viruses and fusarium - critical for Kerala''s humid conditions. Excellent for tropical regions.", "availability": "Konico Seeds, Indian agricultural stores", "sort_order": 4}, {"name": "Hara Meetha Kharbooza (Green Sweet Muskmelon) 🌱", "slug": "hara-meetha-kharbooza-green-sweet-muskmelon", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "India", "traits": "Round, light yellow to green skin, 1.5-2 kg", "flesh_fruit": "Green, super tasty, extremely sweet", "yield_notes": "Prolific fruiting", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 5}, {"name": "Indigenous South Indian Culinary Melons 🏆", "slug": "indigenous-south-indian-culinary-melons", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "", "traits": "", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 6}, {"name": "Vellari / Vellarikka (Culinary Melon) 🏆", "slug": "vellari-vellarikka-culinary-melon", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Kerala, Karnataka, Tamil Nadu (endemic to South India)", "traits": "Elongated to cylindrical shape, green skin, various sizes", "flesh_fruit": "White to pale green, used as vegetable", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "Endemic to tropical humid Southern India. Perfectly adapted to Kerala''s monsoon climate. Grown commercially in seven districts of Kerala. Tremendous diversity in shape, color,