randa-cuspidifolia", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Bolivia to Brazil and Argentina (Salta), native to seasonally dry tropical regions", "traits": "Deciduous tree 4-8m (up to 20m in nature), more compact inflorescences than J. mimosifolia, pointed bipinnate leaves", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Very dependable heavy bloomer annually, more reliable than J. mimosifolia", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Gardino Nursery (Florida, ships to Australia), specialty collectors, harder to find than J. mimosifolia", "sort_order": 3}, {"name": "Jacaranda obtusifolia", "slug": "jacaranda-obtusifolia", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "South Tropical America (Trinidad, Tobago, Venezuela), wet tropical biome", "traits": "Deciduous tree/large shrub 6-11m height, broader less-pinnate leaves than other Jacarandas, denser foliage, rounded canopy", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Moderate flowering, striking color", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Rare in cultivation, botanical gardens, specialty nurseries only", "sort_order": 4}, {"name": "Jacaranda copaia", "slug": "jacaranda-copaia", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Central & South Tropical America (Amazon Basin), wet tropical biome", "traits": "Tall tree 15-30m+ height, straight cylindrical trunk, large bipinnate leaves, narrow crown", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Moderate flowering, valued more for timber than ornamental flowers", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Specialty tropical nurseries, botanical institutions, forestry suppliers", "sort_order": 5}, {"name": "Historical Brisbane/Queensland Plantings", "slug": "historical-brisbane-queensland-plantings", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "", "traits": "", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "Brisbane received mature Jacaranda plants, seedlings and seeds from around the world starting 1855. Major street plantings occurred 1930s-1970s during beautification programs. Trees were offered free to residents in 1970s with conditions. Some original 1914 New Farm Park trees have fallen due to age (100+ years). Goodna has some of Southeast Queensland''s best Jacaranda displays from 1932 plantings", "availability": "", "sort_order": 6}, {"name": "Jacaranda mimosifolia (Neeli Gulmohar/Neel Mohar)", "slug": "jacaranda-mimosifolia-neeli-gulmohar-neel-mohar", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "South America, introduced to India via colonial period, widely planted in Kerala", "traits": "Deciduous tree 8-15m height in Kerala conditions, fern-like pinnate leaves, rounded crown 10-12m spread", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Prolific flowering, spectacular display during blooming season", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Nurserylive (all India delivery), Plantsguru, Exotic Flora (Kadiyam nursery, all India), Garden World, Greenverz, local Kerala nurseries", "sort_order": 0}, {"name": "Jacaranda mimosifolia ''Alba'' (White Jacaranda)", "slug": "jacaranda-mimosifolia-alba-white-jacaranda", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Cultivar selection, rare in India", "traits": "Similar growth to purple form, 8-12m height in tropical conditions", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Sparser blooms than purple but extended season", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Very limited in India, specialty orders only, Amazon India (seeds occasionally)", "sort_order": 1}, {"name": "Jacaranda copaia (Caroba, Para-para)", "slug": "jacaranda-copaia-caroba-para-para", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Amazon Basin, Central/South America", "traits": "Tall fast-growing tree 20-35m, straight trunk, pioneer species", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Moderate flowering, valued for timber and rapid growth", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Forestry nurseries, agroforestry suppliers, specialty tropical plant sources", "sort_order": 2}, {"name": "Jacaranda caroba", "slug": "jacaranda-caroba", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Brazil (Atlantic Forest, cerrado regions)", "traits": "Smaller tree/shrub 4-10m, leathery dark green leaves, adapted to dry savanna but tolerant", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Moderate flowering", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Rare in India, ethnobotanical/medicinal plant nurseries, botanical gardens", "sort_order": 3}, {"name": "Jacaranda jasminoides (Maroon Jacaranda)", "slug": "jacaranda-jasminoides-maroon-jacaranda", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Brazil, Paraguay, Argentina", "traits": "Smaller tree/shrub 3-8m height, compact growth", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Good flowering for size", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Specialty ornamental nurseries, limited availability in India", "sort_order": 4}, {"name": "Jacaranda jasminoides ''Maroon''", "slug": "jacaranda-jasminoides-maroon", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Cultivar of J. jasminoides", "traits": "Compact 3-8m height, fine green foliage", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Reliable blooming in warm climates", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Rare cultivar, specialty collectors, ornamental plant nurseries", "sort_order": 5}, {"name": "Jacaranda caucana", "slug": "jacaranda-caucana", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Colombia, Panama", "traits": "Medium tree 6-12m, rounded canopy, attractive foliage", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Good flowering in humid tropics", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Very rare in India, botanical institutions, specialty tropical collectors", "sort_order": 6}, {"name": "Jacaranda cuspidifolia", "slug": "jacaranda-cuspidifolia", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "Bolivia, Brazil, Argentina - seasonally dry tropical", "traits": "4-8m tree, compact globose inflorescences", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Very dependable heavy annual bloomer", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Rare in India, specialty imports, botanical collections", "sort_order": 7}, {"name": "Colonial Era Munnar Plantings", "slug": "colonial-era-munnar-plantings", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "", "traits": "", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "Jacaranda and Spathodea trees planted by British officials near estate bungalows at same time. Spathodea controlled mosquitoes for malaria prevention. Jacaranda bloom (February-April) indicates spring season in hill stations. Trees planted atop hills and along roadsides for beautification. Create ''river of purple'' effect during peak bloom with tea plantation green background", "availability": "", "sort_order": 8}], "variety_count": 16}'::jsonb,
