satile pollinator with extended bloom time. Also adds ornamental value with attractive foliage. Hardy to Zone 7. Excellent for Saanichton pairing.", "availability": "Australian nurseries, Queensland suppliers", "sort_order": 12}, {"name": "Hayward", "slug": "hayward", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "New Zealand, named after Hayward Wright, 1920s-1930s, introduced commercially 1940s", "traits": "Large oval fruit (120-150g), fuzzy brown skin, world standard variety, 90% of commercial production", "flesh_fruit": "Bright emerald-green flesh, excellent sweet-tangy flavor, high vitamin C, superior quality", "yield_notes": "Very productive, reliable high yields once established", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 13}, {"name": "Hayward", "slug": "hayward", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "New Zealand, 1920s-1930s", "traits": "Large oval fruit, fuzzy brown skin, world''s most cultivated variety", "flesh_fruit": "Bright green flesh, excellent sweet-tangy flavor, high vitamin C", "yield_notes": "Very productive in suitable climates", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 0}, {"name": "Allison", "slug": "allison", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "New Zealand, 1920s", "traits": "Medium oblong fruit, densely hairy skin, early maturing", "flesh_fruit": "Light-green flesh, good balanced flavor", "yield_notes": "Good reliable yields", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 1}, {"name": "Abbott", "slug": "abbott", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "New Zealand, 1920s-1930s", "traits": "Early flowering, medium round fruit, densely hairy", "flesh_fruit": "Very sweet, lower acid content", "yield_notes": "Productive, bears early", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 2}, {"name": "Bruno", "slug": "bruno", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "New Zealand, 1930s-1940s", "traits": "Large elongated fruit, dark brown dense hairs", "flesh_fruit": "Light-green flesh, good flavor, high vitamin C", "yield_notes": "Very vigorous, large crops", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 3}, {"name": "Monty (Montgomery)", "slug": "monty-montgomery", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "New Zealand, chance seedling discovered early 1950s, introduced 1957", "traits": "Small to medium oblong fruit, somewhat angular, widest at apex, dense hairs", "flesh_fruit": "Light-green flesh, good flavor", "yield_notes": "Highly vigorous and productive, sometimes excessively so, late-ripening", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 4}, {"name": "Tomuri (Male)", "slug": "tomuri-male", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "New Zealand", "traits": "Late-blooming male, vigorous growth", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "One male pollinates 8 females", "growing_notes": "RECOMMENDED FOR KERALA - Most commonly used male pollinator in India. Widely recommended by Indian agricultural authorities. Extended bloom covers late-flowering females. Essential for commercial orchards. Vigorous growth needs management in Kerala''s fertile conditions.", "availability": "Widely available from Indian nurseries", "sort_order": 5}, {"name": "Matua (Male)", "slug": "matua-male", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "New Zealand", "traits": "Early to mid-season blooming, vigorous", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "One male pollinates up to 8 females", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 6}, {"name": "Hort16A (Zespri Gold)", "slug": "hort16a-zespri-gold", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "New Zealand, HortResearch breeding program, developed 1991, launched 1997-2000", "traits": "Smooth bronze skin with short silky hair, medium to large fruit, pointed tip", "flesh_fruit": "Bright yellow flesh, tropical sweet flavor (notes of pineapple/mango), less acidic than green", "yield_notes": "Productive, blooms 4 weeks ahead of Hayward", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 7}, {"name": "Jintao (Jin Gold)", "slug": "jintao-jin-gold", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "China, selected 1981 by Wuhan Institute of Botany from wild plants in Jiangxi Province, commercial 2001", "traits": "Golden-yellow smooth skin, medium fruit, highly productive, robust", "flesh_fruit": "Yellow flesh, exceptional sweetness, high sugar content, aromatic", "yield_notes": "Highly productive, earlier than Hayward, disease-resistant", "growing_notes": "SUITABLE FOR KERALA HILLS - Chinese origin may suit subcontinental conditions better. More robust and disease-resistant than Hort16A. Widely grown in China and Italy. Similar quality to Zespri Gold. High essential amino acids. Adapts to various climatic conditions. Good shelf life.", "availability": "May be available through Indian agricultural research institutes", "sort_order": 8}, {"name": "Hongyang (Red Heart Kiwi)", "slug": "hongyang-red-heart-kiwi", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "China, Sichuan Province, seeds collected 1982, officially registered 1997", "traits": "Cylindrical fruit flattened at ends, smooth brown slightly hairy skin, medium size (90g average, up to 150g)", "flesh_fruit": "Red-purple flesh around core radiating outward, yellow-green outer flesh, striking decorative appearance, sweet aromatic tropical taste, few or no seeds", "yield_notes": "Precocious, high field production, most widely planted variety in China", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 9}], "variety_count": 24}'::jsonb,
